245
00:27:15,440 --> 00:27:17,179
Where am I?

246
00:27:17,179 --> 00:27:19,459
Why am I here?

247
00:27:37,699 --> 00:27:40,659
Is this the burial mounds described in books?

248
00:27:41,470 --> 00:27:45,850
(noises)

249
00:27:45,850 --> 00:27:48,480
(noises)

250
00:27:50,100 --> 00:27:51,600
Oh my!

251
00:27:52,119 --> 00:27:54,559
Everyone, did you hear something?

252
00:27:54,559 --> 00:27:56,359
No, I didn't.

253
00:27:56,839 --> 00:27:59,000
Is there anyone out there?

254
00:27:59,419 --> 00:28:02,400
Give me a hand! Help!

255
00:28:02,400 --> 00:28:03,680
The gates of hell have opened!

256
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:06,300
Help!

257
00:28:07,780 --> 00:28:09,880
N-N-Niu!

258
00:28:11,060 --> 00:28:14,259
Wang Daniu, get your behind back here!

259
00:28:15,900 --> 00:28:17,800
Miss?

260
00:28:21,979 --> 00:28:23,755
Miss? Miss?

261
00:28:23,755 --> 00:28:26,600
Young lady, wake up! Are you all right?

262
00:28:34,079 --> 00:28:36,879
Thank goodness. She didn't die of fright.

263
00:28:36,879 --> 00:28:38,919
If she did, that would've caused a horrible misunderstanding.

264
00:28:39,880 --> 00:28:41,019
I'm sorry.

265
00:28:41,019 --> 00:28:43,519
I didn't mean to startle everyone.

266
00:28:44,039 --> 00:28:47,359
But you all are way too cowardly.

267
00:28:51,580 --> 00:28:53,000
Well, be it.

268
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:59,500
The date, place, and hour right now make such a misunderstanding totally understandable.

269
00:29:01,659 --> 00:29:04,240
But why am I here?

270
00:29:11,820 --> 00:29:14,459
I should find a place for a bath first.

271
00:29:15,640 --> 00:29:16,960
Young lady, lie there for now.

272
00:29:16,960 --> 00:29:19,379
I'll get someone to collect you later.

273
00:29:25,659 --> 00:29:27,839
I'm such a gorgeous woman.

274
00:29:27,839 --> 00:29:31,339
Why did I end up in unmarked burial mounds?

275
00:29:32,939 --> 00:29:36,140
Let me recall the story's plot.

276
00:29:37,300 --> 00:29:39,200
Got it.

277
00:29:39,200 --> 00:29:42,880
As the top beauty of the martial arts world, the strongest martial artist fell in love with me at first sight.

278
00:29:42,880 --> 00:29:47,780
After that, the young lords of the various sects were besotted by my beauty as well.

279
00:29:47,780 --> 00:29:49,440
As a result, a war broke out in the martial arts world.

280
00:29:49,440 --> 00:29:52,260
Even the imperial court was involved.

281
00:29:52,260 --> 00:29:56,960
The current emperor and aristocrats were captivated by me too.

282
00:29:56,960 --> 00:30:01,219
In order to win my heart, the world spiraled into chaos.

283
00:30:02,440 --> 00:30:05,640
In the end, I could only sacrifice my own life

284
00:30:05,640 --> 00:30:10,359
to ensure the peace of the martial arts world and the entire country.

285
00:30:14,240 --> 00:30:15,960
- Miss Ye!
- Wait for me!

286
00:30:15,960 --> 00:30:18,039
- Miss Ye!
- Miss Ye!

287
00:30:18,039 --> 00:30:20,480
- Miss Ye, wait for me!
- Miss Ye!

288
00:30:20,480 --> 00:30:22,440
- Beautiful lady!
- Miss Ye!

289
00:30:22,440 --> 00:30:23,960
Beautiful lady!

290
00:30:23,960 --> 00:30:25,860
Miss Ye!

291
00:30:26,680 --> 00:30:28,880
Miss Ye!

292
00:30:28,880 --> 00:30:30,000
Don't jump!

293
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:31,400
Don't jump down!

294
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:33,639
No!

295
00:30:33,639 --> 00:30:35,680
Beautiful lady!

296
00:30:35,680 --> 00:30:38,159
No!

297
00:30:41,640 --> 00:30:42,799
No, that's not it.

298
00:30:42,799 --> 00:30:44,739
The story didn't go like that.

299
00:30:44,739 --> 00:30:50,360
I'm sure they had their reasons for not jumping after me to save me.

300
00:30:50,360 --> 00:30:51,960
One thing's for certain.

301
00:30:51,960 --> 00:30:54,540
They were deeply in love with me.

302
00:30:54,540 --> 00:30:58,300
After my death, they lost all desire to live.

303
00:30:58,300 --> 00:31:00,680
They committed suicide for love.

304
00:31:03,640 --> 00:31:06,039
Unfortunately, such foolish devotion.

305
00:31:06,039 --> 00:31:09,280
Beautiful women truly suffer cursed lives.

306
00:31:09,799 --> 00:31:12,260
Those stories are false.

307
00:31:12,260 --> 00:31:15,119
I heard those villagers talk about a ghost sighting at the burial mounds.

308
00:31:15,119 --> 00:31:18,019
I thought there'd be something exciting in store.

309
00:31:18,780 --> 00:31:20,580
So, it's just you.

310
00:31:21,359 --> 00:31:25,820
How can there be someone so handsome in this world?

311
00:31:26,740 --> 00:31:29,039
You're really alive.

312
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:33,510
Hey.

313
00:31:33,510 --> 00:31:38,020
An ordinary man bumping into a lady bathing would leave at once to avoid suspicion.

314
00:31:38,020 --> 00:31:39,920
You aren't just staying put, but you're staring.

315
00:31:39,920 --> 00:31:42,219
You didn't even blink once.

316
00:31:42,219 --> 00:31:46,559
But... why are you so composed?

317
00:31:52,119 --> 00:31:54,319
Am I not pretty enough?

318
00:31:54,319 --> 00:31:56,280
That's impossible.

319
00:31:58,621 --> 00:31:59,759
I got it.

320
00:31:59,759 --> 00:32:03,940
I bet your courtship was rejected by me and you resent me to this day.

321
00:32:03,940 --> 00:32:05,480
You have to get this through your head.

322
00:32:05,480 --> 00:32:09,859
A stunning beauty like me is very hard to woo.

323
00:32:09,859 --> 00:32:13,600
Why has she become so narcissistic after her resurrection?

324
00:32:13,600 --> 00:32:17,979
Perhaps she was duped too miserably in her past life, so her subconscious is in denial.

325
00:32:18,419 --> 00:32:20,519
Repeat yourself.

326
00:32:23,240 --> 00:32:26,699
I have no impression of you, but your attitude toward me is horrible.

327
00:32:26,699 --> 00:32:30,240
All I can construe is hatred borne from love.

328
00:32:32,219 --> 00:32:35,759
Were you the culprit who buried me at the burial mounds?

329
00:32:37,100 --> 00:32:39,140
As expected, she has lost her memory.

330
00:32:41,079 --> 00:32:43,140
Do you know me?

331
00:32:43,140 --> 00:32:44,440
What is my name?

332
00:32:44,440 --> 00:32:46,659
I really can't remember.

333
00:32:50,699 --> 00:32:55,219
Well... it's a little chilly at night.

334
00:32:55,219 --> 00:32:58,680
How about we speak after I get out of here?

335
00:32:59,440 --> 00:33:01,559
We can let bygones by bygones.

336
00:33:01,559 --> 00:33:06,159
Since we've met again, can you lend me some clothes?

337
00:33:06,739 --> 00:33:09,359
By the way, what's your name?

338
00:33:09,359 --> 00:33:11,980
Should I call you "Older Brother"?

339
00:33:14,519 --> 00:33:18,039
Kind Brother, I'm begging you.

340
00:33:21,359 --> 00:33:23,839
Kind Brother! Don't leave!

341
00:33:23,839 --> 00:33:25,739
Kind Brother!

342
00:33:28,599 --> 00:33:30,400
Kind Brother! Wait up!

343
00:33:30,400 --> 00:33:32,200
Hold on!

344
00:33:47,839 --> 00:33:49,380
The Yin energy here is too potent.

345
00:33:49,380 --> 00:33:53,520
Her blood clots need to be expelled. Otherwise, there might be further implications.

346
00:33:53,520 --> 00:33:54,720
Thank you, Kind Brother!

347
00:33:54,720 --> 00:33:56,359
Don't call me that.

348
00:33:56,359 --> 00:33:58,240
Who knows where you picked that up from?

349
00:33:58,240 --> 00:33:59,720
Don't you have any sense of shame?

350
00:33:59,720 --> 00:34:01,079
Fine, all right.

351
00:34:01,079 --> 00:34:03,720
I'll stop calling you that.

352
00:34:06,839 --> 00:34:08,800
Well, can you tell me—

353
00:34:08,800 --> 00:34:11,199
Listen up, your name is Wang Tieshuan.

354
00:34:11,199 --> 00:34:12,679
No way.

355
00:34:12,679 --> 00:34:15,019
I'm so pretty. How can I have such a name?

356
00:34:15,019 --> 00:34:19,620
Is that so? I'm so handsome, but you don't seem to have any memory of me either.

357
00:34:20,079 --> 00:34:21,840
Wang Village is the closest place around.

358
00:34:21,840 --> 00:34:23,920
There's the folk saying that a plain name ensures a good life.

359
00:34:23,920 --> 00:34:26,920
So, it isn't unusual for you to have such a name.

360
00:34:27,740 --> 00:34:30,159
That does make sense.

361
00:34:30,159 --> 00:34:31,960
But that name is such a bad fit for me.

362
00:34:31,960 --> 00:34:35,020
Well, is the burial mounds a place for a stunning beauty?

363
00:34:35,760 --> 00:34:40,319
Every single martial artist and aristocrat are head over heels for you.

364
00:34:40,319 --> 00:34:42,880
Yet, you've been dumped in the burial mounds.

365
00:34:42,880 --> 00:34:45,480
In the end, not a single person came to collect your body.

366
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:50,300
I wonder what story has such a horribly flawed plot.

367
00:34:50,300 --> 00:34:52,280
How could you eavesdrop on me?

368
00:34:52,280 --> 00:34:54,800
You were the one hollering away.

369
00:34:58,000 --> 00:35:00,000
She still seems very frail.

370
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:01,679
I have to take her to the city to recuperate at once.

371
00:35:01,679 --> 00:35:03,760
Can you rein in that sharp tongue?

372
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:05,039
I'm about to puke blood from anger.

373
00:35:05,039 --> 00:35:06,679
Well, puke it out.

374
00:35:06,679 --> 00:35:09,499
You have way too many enemies anyway. I'm sure you won't live for long.

375
00:35:09,499 --> 00:35:12,259
I have many enemies? What do you mean by that?

376
00:35:12,259 --> 00:35:13,719
Come into the city with me.

377
00:35:13,719 --> 00:35:15,419
I'll explain to you then.

378
00:35:17,760 --> 00:35:20,299
I'm not following you into the city.

379
00:35:28,360 --> 00:35:31,719
Explain what you mean by having many enemies.

380
00:35:31,719 --> 00:35:33,320
I can't tell you yet.

381
00:35:33,320 --> 00:35:35,559
If you want to find out, come with me.

382
00:35:35,559 --> 00:35:37,159
Make your choice.

383
00:35:37,159 --> 00:35:41,060
Why are you bent on taking me into the city? Are you a twisted human trafficker?

384
00:35:41,060 --> 00:35:43,779
Are you planning to sell me to the city's brothel?

385
00:35:46,679 --> 00:35:49,559
W-Wait! C-Calm down!

386
00:35:49,559 --> 00:35:53,399
I'll go with you, b-but I can't be dressed like this.

387
00:35:53,399 --> 00:35:55,679
Find me some clothes.

388
00:36:11,510 --> 00:36:16,520
”Waiting” - Li Hongyi

389
00:36:16,520 --> 00:36:22,130
♫ How many stories have you heard of the Mortal World? ♫

390
00:36:22,130 --> 00:36:28,280
♫ Dressing in light clothes, I've become forgotten in the horizon ♫

391
00:36:28,280 --> 00:36:34,150
♫ I can’t bear to go home again ♫

392
00:36:34,150 --> 00:36:39,550
♫ And I can’t seem to find your voice to accompany me ♫

393
00:36:39,550 --> 00:36:45,470
♫ The sound of the melodious song leisurely stirs up the past ♫

394
00:36:45,470 --> 00:36:51,270
♫ My long-cherished wish has not been fulfilled, how can I leave you? ♫

395
00:36:51,270 --> 00:36:57,030
♫ How could destiny take me back to that city? ♫

396
00:36:57,030 --> 00:37:02,890
♫ To find the warmth you left behind ♫

397
00:37:02,890 --> 00:37:08,910
♫ A gentle dream becomes reality magnifying the roads I’ve taken ♫

398
00:37:08,910 --> 00:37:14,660
♫ Laughing and sighing in this life, why bother asking if I’d be interested in it again? ♫

399
00:37:14,660 --> 00:37:20,640
♫ Why is there someone willing to wait without knowing the pain and resentment? ♫

400
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:26,480
♫ It’s hard to tell stories of the past ♫

401
00:37:26,480 --> 00:37:35,270
♫ Unintentionally, like the trees and grass, I’m foolishly hoping for true love ♫

402
00:37:35,270 --> 00:37:45,580
♫ I will wait for you for the rest of my life ♫
